Feature Details

1. Password Storage and Autofill

Passwords sync across all devices where user is signed into Edge with their work account
Export available as CSV, device authentication required before export
Passwords can be imported from Chrome or any browser via CSV
Chrome passwords can be moved to Edge so they are managed and monitored by IT

2. Password Monitor

Scans saved passwords for three risks, leaked, reused and weak
Shows exactly which sites are affected
Direct Change button takes user to that site's password change page
No email notification, alert appears inside Edge settings only
Admin can enforce this feature via policy, users cannot turn it off

3. Azure AD Single Sign-On (SSO)

Users sign in once with their work account and access all apps automatically, no repeated logins
Tested on portal.office.com, signed in automatically without credentials
Tested on non-Microsoft apps, JIRA, Confluence and Bitbucket all signed in via work account
MFA verified once for JIRA, Confluence and Bitbucket signed in automatically in the same session

4. Extension Monitoring

Gives IT visibility into all browser extensions installed across company devices
30 extensions found installed across the organisation
Shows how many users have each extension
Individual user details not visible, only total user count per extension
Risk level of extensions not shown

5. Secure Password Deployment

Policy deployed and received by Edge, autofill testing pending

Observations

Usability

Pros
No additional deployment required, EPM is built into Edge already installed on company devices
No user training needed, password saving autofill and SSO work automatically
Microsoft provides free training resources and documentation on their website
User interface is clean and easy to understand
One click password security scan, checks leaked reused and weak passwords
Strong password suggestions built in
Chrome passwords can be imported to Edge in one step

Cons
Password age not visible to users
Breach alerts only appear inside Edge settings, users must actively check
No email notification when a breach is detected
Only works in Edge, Chrome users are not covered

Adaptability

Pros
Works with Microsoft apps like SharePoint, Teams, Outlook out of the box
Also works with non-Microsoft tools, tested on JIRA, Confluence, Bitbucket and GitHub
Works on Windows, Mac, iPhone and Android
Policy follows the user, works on any device they sign into Edge with their work account
Chrome passwords can be moved to Edge easily using import feature
Microsoft regularly updates EPM at no extra cost

Cons
Does not work on Chrome, employees using Chrome are not covered
For non-Microsoft apps like JIRA, IT needs to do a one-time setup before SSO works
Deploying shared passwords needs careful setup, wrong URL or username format will cause it to fail

Scalability

Pros
Works for organisations of any size, no limit on number of users or devices
Admin can create and apply policies to specific groups or all users at once
No device enrollment needed for cloud policies, easy to roll out to new employees
New employees automatically get all policies when they sign into Edge with their work account

Cons
Works best when everyone uses Edge, if employees use Chrome coverage is incomplete
For stricter control on company devices, IT needs Intune access on top of EPM
Shared password deployment needs a real shared account, cannot be used for personal accounts
